        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 11 at 7:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 714 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Faunsdale, or 7 miles west of Uniontown, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Newbern, Demopolis, Vaiden, Old Spring Hill, Gallion,
Folsom, Faunsdale, Arcola, Heiberger, Uniontown, Birdine, Harper
Hill, Vaiden Field Airport, Laneville, Havana, Perry County
Correctional Center, Judson College, Greensboro Municipal Airport,
and Morgan Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
